729835f-a.title: Richmond: Victory Boulevard - Bryson Avenue
729835f-a.text:
Victory Boulevard, at the N.E. corner of Bryson (formerly Decatur) Avenue. The inscription over the window readsf Carbureter
Expert.
April 26, 1929
P. L. Sperr

729814f-a.title: Richmond: Victory Boulevard - Decatur Avenue
729814f-a.text:
2444 Victory Boulevard, at the S.E. corner of Decatur Avenue, showing the A. Schults residence (1932). The house was owned by F. Trits in 1874 and by M. Mulveney
from 1898 to 1917.
May 19, 1932
P. L. Sperr
